---
// src/pages/projects/puppypov.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="PuppyPOV Architecture | Ean Cummings">
  <article class="project-deep-dive animate-fade-in">
    
    <!-- ==================== 1. CINEMATIC HEADER ==================== -->
    <header class="project-hero">
      <div class="project-hero-container">
        <span class="pro-tag-badge">Connected Vitals & Edge IoT</span>
        <h1 class="pro-headline">PuppyPOV</h1>
        <p class="pro-subheading">
          A wearable smart harness designed to solve biometric tracking anomalies by correlating continuous physiological health metrics with physical environmental context.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-overlay"></div>
    </header>

    <!-- ==================== 2. SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE BLOCK ==================== -->
    <section class="pro-content-row">
      <div class="pro-sidebar">
        <span class="row-num">01 / System Design</span>
        <h2>Edge DSP & Interface Architecture</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="pro-main-body">
        <p>
          The core challenge of wearable canine biometrics is isolating true cardiac signals from massive physical motion artifacts. To resolve this, the system processes raw reflected light signals from the <strong>MAX30102 pulse oximeter</strong> directly on an <strong>Adafruit Feather</strong> tied to an <strong>Arduino Nano 33 BLE Sense</strong> hardware stack.
        </p>
        <p>
          I engineered a custom digital signal processing pipeline on the microcontroller, incorporating a <strong>3rd-order Butterworth bandpass filter (0.8Hz - 3.0Hz)</strong>, median-filtered peak detection algorithms with an intrinsic refractory period to prevent physiologically impossible heart rate readings, and 20% exponential smoothing algorithms to yield stable, reliable vitals while in motion.
        </p>
        
        <!-- Premium Dual Photo Showcase Grid -->
        <div class="product-media-gallery">
          <div class="media-panel-box">
            <img src="/images/puppypov-web.png" alt="PuppyPOV Web Dashboard Interface Mockup" class="media-photo" />
            <span class="media-caption">Dashboard monitoring live vitals, and outlier thresholds.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="media-panel-box">
            <img src="/images/loki-harness.jpg" alt="Loki Wearing the Wearable IoT Smart Harness Prototype" class="media-photo" />
            <span class="media-caption">Hardware field verification run on Loki wearing the multi-sensor integrated smart harness.</span>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ==================== 3. HARDWARE DIAGRAM & TOPOLOGY LAYER ==================== -->
    <section class="pro-content-row">
      <div class="pro-sidebar">
        <span class="row-num">02 / Topology</span>
        <h2>Hardware Integration & Data Topology</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="pro-main-body">
        <p>
          The hardware topology is divided into a centralized edge gateway and a secure, sandboxed wireless endpoint. Wired I2C and serial interfaces tie the peripheral sensors directly to a <strong>Raspberry Pi central gateway</strong>, minimizing external wireless vulnerabilities.
        </p>
        <p>
          Whenever the gateway thread registers an accelerated biometric anomaly surpassing pre-configured thresholds, it commands an event-triggered <strong>PiCam capture event</strong>. This image payload is appended as a Base64 string directly within JSON packets to give real-time environmental context to the user.
        </p>
        
        <!-- Large Centerpiece System Diagram Container -->
        <div class="system-diagram-container">
          <img src="/images/puppypov-diagram.png" alt="PuppyPOV Hardware and Cloud Data Flow Schematic Diagram" class="diagram-photo" />
          <span class="media-caption">Complete system layout mapping hardware bus lines, centralized local server ingest endpoints, and dual cloud databases.</span>
        </div>

        <!-- Tech Spec Data Architecture Breakdown Table -->
        <div class="topology-specs-box">
          <div class="topo-row">
            <span class="topo-label">Local Edge Bus</span>
            <span class="topo-value">Wired 5V, GND, SDA, and SCL I2C lines from MAX30102 to Adafruit Feather</span>
          </div>
          <div class="topo-row">
            <span class="topo-label">Gateway Ingest</span>
            <span class="topo-value">Multithreaded Python gateway managing local store-and-forward connection monitors</span>
          </div>
          <div class="topo-row">
            <span class="topo-label">Network Transport</span>
            <span class="topo-value">HTTPS POST requests via TLS encryption with an application layer shared secret token</span>
          </div>
          <div class="topo-row">
            <span class="topo-label">Cloud Databases</span>
            <span class="topo-value">InfluxDB (high-frequency time-series sensors) & Firebase (user profiles & media blobs)</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ==================== 4. TECH SPECS DASHBOARD ==================== -->
    <section class="pro-content-row border-top-only">
      <div class="pro-sidebar">
        <span class="row-num">03 / Tech Specs</span>
        <h2>System Specifications</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="pro-main-body">
        <div class="specs-mini-grid">
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Microcontrollers</h4>
            <p>Arduino Nano 33 BLE Sense & Adafruit Feather M4</p>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Local Display</h4>
            <p>128x64 OLED status screen panel</p>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Sensors Built-In</h4>
            <p>MAX30102 PPG Optoelectronics, Accelerometer, Microphone, PiCam</p>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Security Core</h4>
            <p>Hashed passwords, client signature validation, TLS streams</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</Layout>

<!-- ==================== STYLES ==================== -->
<style>
  .project-deep-dive {
    max-width: 1024px;
    width: min(100%, 92%);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 80px 0;
  }

  /* --- Advanced Hero Styling Layering --- */
  .project-hero {
    min-height: 50vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding-top: 80px;
    padding-bottom: 60px;
    background-color: #000000;
  }

  /* Using a pseudo-element layers the photo cleanly beneath grid mask */
  .project-hero::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4) 0%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.75) 65%, #000000 92%, #000000 100%), url('/images/puppypov-bg.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .project-hero-container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 10;
    padding: 0 4px;
  }

  .pro-tag-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--accent-blue);
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid rgba(47, 128, 237, 0.4);
    border-radius: 100px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
  }

  .pro-headline {
    font-size: 4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 20px 0;
    color: #ffffff;
    text-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.75), 0 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  }

  .pro-subheading {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: #e8e8ed;
    max-width: 720px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
    text-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
  }

  .grid-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: radial-gradient(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 32px 32px;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  /* --- Row Layout Mechanics --- */
  .pro-content-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 40px;
    padding: 64px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .border-top-only {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .pro-content-row {
      grid-template-columns: 3fr 5fr;
      gap: 64px;
    }
    .pro-sidebar {
      position: sticky;
      top: 100px;
    }
  }

  .row-num {
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .pro-sidebar h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .pro-main-body {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .pro-main-body p {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  /* --- Upgraded Dual Photo Showcase Grid --- */
  .product-media-gallery {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 32px;
    width: 100%;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .product-media-gallery {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .media-panel-box {
    background: #0d0d0e;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .media-photo {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 240px; 
    object-fit: cover; 
    object-position: top center; 
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: block;
  }

  .media-caption {
    display: block;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 10px;
    padding: 0 4px;
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* --- Centerpiece System Diagram Container --- */
  .system-diagram-container {
    margin-top: 32px;
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 20px;
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    background: #0d0d0e;
    padding: 24px;
    box-shadow: 0 30px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .diagram-photo {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 450px; 
    object-fit: contain; 
    display: block;
  }

  /* --- Technical Topology Table --- */
  .topology-specs-box {
    margin-top: 40px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding-top: 16px;
  }

  .topo-row {
    display: flex;
    justify-space: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 14px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .topo-row:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .topo-label {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .topo-value {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 300;
    text-align: right;
    max-width: 65%;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .topo-row {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 4px;
    }
    .topo-value {
      text-align: left;
      max-width: 100%;
    }
  }

  /* --- Technical Spec Breakdown --- */
  .specs-mini-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .spec-mini-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.01);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .spec-mini-card h4 {
    margin: 0 0 6px 0;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .spec-mini-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
</style>